  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Supp voluntary repatriation process for  Burundi</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">UNHCR prioritises voluntary repatriation in conditions of safety and dignity as the best long-term solution to refugee crises worldwide. Implementation of Voluntary repatriation of Burundian refugees from Tanzania started in September 2017. The aim of supporting this programme is to ensure approximately 20,000 refugees were repatriating to Burundi between September to December 2020. Support mainly focused on the repatriation process including verification of the voluntary nature of the return and the required logistics.</narrative>
  </description>
